content.description: Start High in small crimps (may be a stacked pad start). Pull on and with terrible feet make a static move to a cool 2+ finger pinch. After gaining the pinch continue to the top of boulder.
content.location: A round the corner from Dead leaves on the dirty ground.

content.description: This is the perfect arete problem. The feet tend to be good; however, the poor crimps and sloping arete demand balance, precision, and core strength. Sit start low and work your way up the left trending arete!
content.location: The West arete of the Dead Leaves Boulder

content.description: This is the easy slab to the right of the Craft Arete.
content.location: The West fave of the Dead Leaves Boulder

climbs.name: Dead Leaves and the Dirty Ground

content.description:
Start on lowest undercling sitting on the ground. Make a big move up and right to triangle shaped jug. From the triangle make a huge move to the amazing slope and top out, up and right.  

  One of the Best V7's in the midwest.
content.location: On the far left side of the dead leaves boulder.

content.description: Venture into the omnious cave to the West of the Dead Leaves Boulder and you may find a dead animal, because Crack Kills. The ceiling of the cave has an perfect hand crack. Follow this crack out and over the bulge!
content.location: The cave to the West of Dead Leaves Boulder

content.description: Powerful reachy moves gain an easy slab finish.
content.location: Sit start matched on the left facing side pull rail on the main face of the boulder. Make moves right until the arete. Rock over onto arete and finish on the slab.

content.description:
Powerful reachy moves lead to a fantastic finish on the arete. 

  Broccoli Command in the video.
content.location: Sit start matched on the left facing side pull rail on the main face of the boulder. Make moves right until the arete. Then follow Relationship Of Command to the top.
